article.headline: Florida A&M 75, N. Carolina A&T 71
article.story: GREENSBORO, N.C. (AP) -- Tony Tate scored 21 points to lead Florida A&M to a 75-71 victory over winless North Carolina A&T on Saturday. Rome Sanders added 11 points and Michael Sams scored 10, while Jonathan Kelly added 9 points and 13 rebounds to lead the Rattlers (7-9, 3-2 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference). Jason Wills led all scorers with 22 points for the Aggies (0-13, 0-4), while Leslie Powell had 12 points, Greg Roberts scored 11 and Michael Hayes added 10. The Aggies, seeking their first win of the season, shot 43.8 percent from the field in the first half to the Rattlers' 41.7 percent and held a slim 31-30 lead at the break. But Florida A&M came back in the second, shooting 60.7 percent from the field -- 75 percent from 3-point range -- and outscoring North Carolina A&T 45-40 for the win.
